JEE applications should not "getClassLoader"
Why is this an issue? Using the standard getClassLoader() may not return the right class loader in a JEE context. Instead, go through the currentThread. 
### Noncompliant
ClassLoader cl = this.getClass().getClassLoader();  // Noncompliant
### Compliant
ClassLoader cl = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();
### Noncompliant
{{BUGGY}}
### Compliant
